title: What is COVID-19?
description: COVID-19 is a respirator disease caused by coronavirus that can be spread from person to person.

title: What are COVID-19's symptoms?
description: The most common symptoms are very similar to other viruses: fever, cough, and difficulty breathing.

title: Who is at high risk for COVID-19?
description: Everyone is at risk of getting COVID-19, but some people are at a higher risk of serious illness.

title: What about COVID-19, pregnancy, and newborns?
description: At this time, pregnant women reportedly have the same COVID-19 risk as adults who are not pregnant. There is also no clear evidence that a fetus can be infected with COVID-19 in the womb.

title: When should I see a doctor?
description: Knowing when to see a doctor can keep medical care available for those who need it most.
